Random possibly stupid idea to improve search relevance:

Terms that are mentioned near the top of a page are probably more important than terms that only appear down the bottom.

So index the top of the page (2kbytes? 200 words? Look at average pages in our own content to see how long it is, we really want "the top third of the average-sized page that isn't just a quick one- or two-liner") separately, and when searching, give hits that occur in the top part more weight than those that don't.

